## 8. Hooks Organization

### useActionHandlers Pattern
export function useActionHandlers(actions, modals, table, playerNumber, ...) {
  const handleAction = useCallback((data) => {
    // Validate
    // Call action
    // Close modal
    // Update UI
  }, [actions, modals, ...]);

  return { handleAction };
}

### Available Game Hooks
- useGameActions: All action dispatchers
- useActionHandlers: Modal handlers
- useModalManager: Modal state management
- useDrag: Drag and drop handling
- useGameState: Game state subscription

---

## 9. Error Handling

### Server Handlers
if (requiredParam) {
  throw new Error('actionName: requiredParam is required');
}

### Client Components
- Use try/catch for async operations
- Display user-friendly errors (toasts, modals)
- Log errors with context: [ComponentName] Error: details

### Logging Pattern
console.log('[ActionName] Description:', relevantData);
// Example:
console.log('[captureOpponent] Capturing build:', targetStackId, 'value:', buildValue);

---

## 10. Testing Conventions

- Test files: __tests__/*.test.ts or *.test.ts
- Server handlers: Unit test with mock state
- Components: Test with different game states
- Integration: Test critical flows (drop → extend → confirm → cancel → turn end)

---

## 11. UI/UX Guidelines

### Badge Styling
- Pill shape (fully rounded corners) for player indicators
- Square with rounded corners for build value badges
- No borders on badges (use shadows for separation)
- Bold text on all badges

### Component Props
- Always use interfaces with JSDoc descriptions
- Use optional props with defaults
- Prefer explicit boolean props

---

## 12. Performance

- Memoize derived values with useMemo
- Callback handlers with useCallback
- Broadcast only deltas (not full state)
- Use requestAnimationFrame for layout measurements

---

## 13. TypeScript Guidelines

- Use interface for object shapes, type for unions/aliases
- Avoid any - use explicit types
- Group imports: external, then internal
- Use strict mode

---

## 14. File Organization Rules

### When Adding New Components
1. Put UI components in components/ui/
2. Put game-specific in components/game/
3. Put modals in components/modals/
4. Put table components in components/table/

### When Adding New Server Actions
1. Add to shared/game/actions/
2. Export from shared/game/actions/index.js
3. Add router logic in shared/game/smart-router/

### When Adding New Hooks
1. Game hooks go in hooks/game/
2. Multiplayer hooks go in hooks/multiplayer/
3. UI hooks go in hooks/

---

## 15. Quick Reference

| Pattern | Rule |
|---------|------|
| Colors | Use getPlayerColors() from constants/teamColors.ts |
| State | Derive from server broadcast, never mirror locally |
| Actions | Route through server, never auto-execute |
| Modals | Always confirm + cancel, close after dispatch |
| Errors | Throw descriptive, log with [Module] prefix |
| Imports | React → External → Internal absolute → Relative |
| Naming | Components: PascalCase, hooks: useCamelCase, files: PascalCase.tsx |

